details.description:
Charlotte's most lush cocktail bar is now an ALL DAY cafe in the heart of South End. Start in the morning with coffee and espresso by local roaster Night Swim Coffee—plus flavored syrups and mushroom-based wellness shots—paired with savory and sweet breakfast bites by Built On Hospitality executive Chef Chris Coleman. The Noon & Night menu features bold, craveable flavors for lunch, dinner, and everything in between (and after).
Cocktail service begins at 10 a.m. on weekends and 2 p.m. on weekdays. Enjoy a Bob Peters creation with your brunch, afternoon calls, or when the workday is done. Reservations accepted and 21+ after 5pm, daily.

reviews_data.review_text: One star. Stopped by Folia on a Saturday night around 9pm after my phone died while waiting for an Uber. Security was fine, but the hostess staff was unhelpful and just got the manager, who immediately told me to leave instead of offering any assistance. I had cash in hand and just needed to charge my phone for a few minutes to get home safely. Really disappointed by how rude and dismissive the staff were—definitely not the hospitality I expected. Was looking forward to checking this place out eventually, but will not be returning.
Cocktail, foods, vibe, and service 10/10!!!!

review_questions.Noise level: Loud, but you can still talk

reviews_data.review_text: Too loud, slow and inconsiderate environment.

Cool concept, good service, pretty cocktails. Very aesthetic and so are the employees. I’d like to see a male bartender in tight shorts next time. Only con is that it’s difficult to have a conversation when it’s busy. It’s not a big place. You’re literally shoulder to shoulder at the bar. A bit uncomfortable for me and probably for the stranger next to me.

review_questions.Noise level: Loud, but you can still talk

reviews_data.review_text: This is a great place to stop in for a drink. The service I received from Kayleigh, Rylee, and Kaila was amazing and welcoming. 10/10 will be back.

Such an awesome experience! Highly recommend to anyone who wants amazing drinks, the prefect complement to flavorful, unique food, and a relaxed atmosphere. Think throwback without a smoky haze.
Kayleigh was very attentive and responded to our every request quickly, with a smile, and was so knowledgeable about the menu, beverage options, and even neighborhood stories!

Folia is a fabulous place to meet up with friends. Very interesting and upscale but warm and inviting. Food and drinks a top notch! And a special shout out for Kayleigh! She is the best and we always try to go when she is there! Makes the best drinks and is so gregarious, funny and always makes you feel like you belong there!!!
Really cute aesthetic. Best Paloma in Charlotte. Bartender Truly was super nice.
Neat place. Check it out!

review_questions.Seating type: Indoor dining area, Bar area, Booth seating, Counter seating

reviews_data.review_text: This was my first visit to this place, and our server, named“Truly,” was amazing! My girlfriend and I both ordered mocktails, and she created personalized drinks that perfectly matched our preferences. The ambiance, the service, everything was exceptional. I highly recommend this place and will definitely be returning.

I liked this place! Nice environment. We were seated quickly & ordered our drinks, however, our server didn’t come back to ask us if we wanted another even after our drinks were completely empty for quite some time. Drinks were super good!

Atmospherically, I’m sure Folia checks a lot of boxes for cocktail enthusiasts but for a small plate restaurant this is not it.
I made reservations for brunch for my sister’s birthday and when we arrived the greeting could not have been more lackluster. This place is not as advertised.

Brunch was uninspired, and the lack of atmosphere (at least on this Sunday)  made us feel like we weren’t even supposed there. They feature a small menu offering for brunch (which I’m sure might have been great had they not been out of half the menu items on a Sunday for brunch service especially when you open at 12pm)

Our server was very apologetic for the lackluster experience (we didn’t even bring it up) so we had a drink, got the one thing on the menu that was available, and went elsewhere. Save your time and your money.
Great time and intimate setting. Good vibes.
Service was fantastic. Drinks were great, even the mocktails.

The drinks, service and atmosphere are absolute perfection. The sitting areas are comfortable and clean and the noise and music were at a perfect conversational level.
It’s like sitting in the nicest cozy living room where a sweet friend brings you their signature cocktails durning a dinner party.
10 out of 10…BRILLIANT job, Folia! My new fav cocktail bar, hands down.
Like a gardening store speakeasy , very cute! The cocktails were amazing! I was shocked it wasn’t busy at all.
Marjorie was the best!
Mediocre. The atmosphere is ok, nothing special. Couldn’t even get a drink or food because the bartender refused to serve my group. So many better places in Charlotte!
Skip the food and just get coctails.

I understand that Folia is classified as a speakeasy due to its unique entryway—walking through a stylish plant shop before it opens up into the cocktail lounge definitely adds to the intrigue. However, the large glass window clearly showing the bar takes away from that hidden gem, secretive feel I typically associate with a true speakeasy.

The overall ambiance is calming, modern, and unique, making it a nice spot to relax. The cocktails were tasty, but nothing stood out beyond what I’ve had at other cocktail bars. One downside was the lack of a personalized experience—despite having a reservation, no one was at the front to greet us. After waiting nearly 10 minutes, we opened the door ourselves and were simply told to sit wherever we wanted, which diminished that tailored, exclusive touch.

While it’s a cute spot worth checking out, I wouldn’t classify it as a must-see compared to other options in the area.
Christina was so amazing! The drinks were so good and I loved the vibes.
Christina was an excellent server! She made our night ✨🤍 such a cozy vibe

Went for my husband birthday. The staff gave him a bday card and they all signed it. Super surprised by the gesture. The ace is awesome. Ask the bartender to make you an old fashion with elder flower, you wont be disappointed
Atmosphere and vibe was great.  Didn’t get any food just cocktails at the bar.  Drinks were weak and expensive and served by inexperienced bartender.  With tip, 4 drinks were $100.

A Miami oasis of good vibes, delicious small bites, and outstanding cocktails has found its way to SouthEnd and it’s going to be the place to be in Charlotte!

What you can enjoy: Food menu crafted by chef @tylerjordanlong and a cocktail menu crafted by @bobpeters.

MUST-order snack: Octopus — aji amarillo, espelette, and lime (Incredible!!!!)

From the bar, to the patio-like couch seating with water features, and the speakeasy-like lounge seating in the back of the bar, every nook and cranny was perfectly thought out. Come for the well crafted cocktail menu (with non alcoholic options) and stay for the small bites and great service. Pro tip: You can make reservations on Open Table.

I was so excited when I first walked into this lounge being it was my first time coming here. I was hoping to have a great experience since the ambiance and music seemed to be on point but I was rather disappointed from the moment I walked in. The customer service was awful and my friends were treated horribly by the bartender and even management. They had not ordered any drinks and the bartender refused to serve them and said they were intoxicated which wasn't the case at all. Even the security was super rude and made me feel uncomfortable. I had high hopes for this establishment but due to my experience I will not be back.
Very rude staff. Really ruined my experience there
Amazing vibes and unique cocktails. I can't get over how much this place makes me feel like I'm in Blanche Devereaux's floral bedroom...in the absolute best way!
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Amy, all we have to say is: "Thank you for being a friend."
:) 

See you soon!

reviews_data.review_text: A green and floral paradise, with beautiful tropical, bohemian touches throughout the space with amazing service, music, vibes and cocktails! Great spot for date day or date night or to meet up with friends for a little social happy hour! My husband and I went here for our day date and enjoyed some "annuals"- Folia's cocktails that are here for the season. We were thoroughly impressed by the service, the friendliness of the staff and the cocktails themselves! There is an art to making a great cocktail and Folia has done it well! We tried the Honey Franciulli; Drink Ses-a-me, Morning Bourbon! and Banana Nut Bread. All had amazing flavor profiles! Definitely a must try for anyone looking for chill/lounge vibes, some fresh cocktails and plants all-around! *They also have small bites/small plates as well, including a brunch menu served till 3pm on weekends. We tried the Cucumber Avocado Toast (from their brunch menu) and the Octopus (from their regular menu)- both very delish! Thank you for making our day date so much fun! Can't wait to go back!

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Octopus, Banana Nut Bread, Honey Franciulli

reviews_data.owner_answer: Rosie, Thank you so much for taking the time to write such a thoughtful and kind review. We hope we get to hang out again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: When my boyfriend and I walked into the door the older lady at the hostess stand was very rude. When we entered the door we were not greeted, but instead just stared at until I said hello. Keep in mind it was only my boyfriend and I and the hostess standing there. I don’t know what her issue was, but it was like she looked at us like we did not belong there. When we got seated, I will say our bartender Eric saved the day! Eric was great, engaging, and make wonderful cocktails. The hostess lady really put a bad taste in our mouth….
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Kiana, 
Thank you for taking the time to share your experience with us. We're genuinely sorry to hear about the negative impression you had when you first arrived. At our establishment, we strive to provide a warm and welcoming environment for all our guests, and it looks like we missed the mark on this during your visit.

Please know that we take your feedback very seriously and will address this matter with our team to ensure that all our guests receive the friendly and courteous service they deserve from the moment they walk through our doors.

We are thrilled to hear that Eric was able to turn your experience around with his exceptional service and fantastic cocktails. We'll be sure to pass along your kind words to him—it's always wonderful to know when our team members make a positive impact.

We hope you’ll give us another opportunity to serve you in the future and provide the five-star experience we aim for with every visit.

Cheers, 
Team Folia

reviews_data.review_text: The vibe is cute but the security guard at the front was super rude. He did not want to let us in because it was too busy but then the host seated us within a few minutes…as for the cocktails I’m confused because it looked like the bartender just poured them all from a tap? $17 for a pre mixed drink at a “cocktail” bar is crazy.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Lucy, Thanks for taking the time to leave us a review. We do typically work off of reservations so sometimes it does take us a minute to sort through our systems and make sure we are honoring the space we have already promised to guests. I know it appears like we are just pouring drinks on tap, but those are batched cocktails made with house squeezed juices and freshly made syrups. While they do save us time in service, we still put a lot of love into those and use only top quality ingredients. We do appreciate your input and we will try to find ways to add value and make excellent experiences happen for you in the future. Please get in touch any time to book your next reservation or special event!

reviews_data.review_text: Not only was the bartender good but the entire staff was beyond attentive!

reviews_data.review_text: Beautiful cocktail bar, a great staff & amazing drinks! Perfect place for a girls night out or a date night. Always enjoy my time here.
I highly recommend if you are in Southend! Drinks were creative and delicious and will be bringing more friends here next time! The staff was incredibly nice too!

Wow! Such an unique experience in an area typically overrun with bar hoppers. The food here is absolutely a 10/10, you MUST try the Njuda flatbread. All drinks were strong and had a spin on them. For example, my banana nut bread drink literally came with candied nuts on the side and when paired, well you can guess what it tasted like I’m sure! The manager on staff that night, Jaime, was wonderful! Very informative and knowledgeable about the menu and every recommendation she made was spot on. Will be back again! Absolutely adore the “secret” entrance and the speak easy vibes.
Amazing staff. Definitely my go to place when I'm visiting the area.

Really great place hidden away in Southend. Had a great time escaping the hustle and bustle of the neighborhood. Excellent service, cocktails, light fare and a very exciting wine list. Highly recommend reservations, especially on the weekend.

reviews_data.review_text: I love this place. The vibe walking in is always so welcoming. The staff is amazing, ready and willing to ensure you are happy and feel safe in their environment. Can't wait to go again. Of course plants are just amazing.
Amazing atmosphere and super friendly staff!
Me and my twin were there and honestly it was disappointing to see the attitude of the security staff. Please fix your attitude:)
Service was terrible and the staff treats you like cattle . Never going back there again.
I liked the bar esthetic but security is overly aggressive. Also, very slow service.

they didn’t let us in and none of us were intoxicated whatsoever (I promise we had 3 people not drinking at all). They thought they were better than every other bar. I would not go to this bar unless you’re looking to be turned away. Too “prestigious” for my taste. There’s so many better places to go in Charlotte. I will never go back.

The atmosphere here is amazing! The cocktails tasted great, however, at this price point I aimed for a more elevated presentation. We only tried their brunch menu--egg Salad was fantastic and the flatbread was pretty good too.

I recently celebrated my birthday at Folia, and while the entire experience was fantastic, the highlight of our visit was definitely Bria! She went above and beyond to make sure our large group was able to sit together in the Green Room, which really set the tone for an amazing evening. Not only did she accommodate us with a beautiful setup, but we were also treated to complimentary champagne, which was a lovely surprise!

Our server (I wish I could remember her name) was also wonderful—attentive, friendly, and just made us feel so well taken care of.

Bria, thank you so much for making the start of my birthday celebration so special. You truly made it memorable, and because of you, we'll definitely be back. Highly recommend this place, and if you’re lucky enough to have Bria helping you, you're in for an amazing experience!
Folia was great! Atmosphere is a VIBE! Drinks were pretty good. I liked my Claud margarita above anything else. Will definitely be back
Can’t even get into this place. Had reservations twice and they would not let us in. Find another joint in South End to go to.

Such a cute place! Hostess was super sweet- Bartender was great didn’t get his name he was the blonde guy - Oscar was great! I think I met the owner and I can tell the place has her touch because the bathrooms were Conveniently stocked for a woman’s needs- I love that. The decor is gorgeous and comfy and the vibe is very chill and grown. They have a great mock tail menu and appetizers I had the butternut squash flatbread - the baguette - the mango desert and the chocolate cake. 10/10

reviews_data.review_text:
Beautiful place. Peaceful atmosphere. Great friendly bartender Erik made us feel welcomed on our our first visit and made great drinks
Will definitely return 👍👍

Loved this place!!!! The host shout out to her she was amazing!!!!!!! BUT FYI the server did not want to mention the 50 dollar truffle when I went to order the baguette. She never mentioned it was a "special" she just asked if I wanted "caviar or truffle". When I get my bill and see for our server to not mention the truffle being an EXTRA $50 for a $9 baguette was messed up. But overall loved the place will be back and not ordered the truffle 🙌🏽

We went as a group of friends to celebrate my birthday and unfortunately it was overall a rough experience. Although the cocktails and the ambiance/design were very nice the operations and service was VERY poor. Where we had made our reservation for (the green room) which open table specifically had you pick when you make a reservation, we were not sat there. When inquiring about our seating the manager said you cannot request places to sit…so this was just untrue which felt quite sketchy. They gave us a champagne toast to compensate which was nice however. After that the drinks were great but with a party of 4 they came up to our table and told us we had to leave that the next party was there and waiting in the lobby. We hadn’t even been seated for an hour and a half yet. The manager then came up again after we said we needed to then cancel our drink order if we were being kicked out. She apologized and said we could stay and gave us some drinks but just sent us 2 drinks for a party of 4. It was all very uncomfortable and we felt like we were on a time although it doesn’t say a time limit or anything on the reservations. They didn’t have the proper ingredients on a busy Saturday night to make an espresso martini (arguably one of the most popular cocktails right now) and it was quite bad. The manager did try to apologize and check on us but at that point it was just uncomfortable and we were ready to go anyways. I would like to go again when they become better with service and operations and give more specific instructions on what their reservations look like as the ambiance and cocktails were good but this specific experience was poor.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hello, Thanks for taking the time to share your feedback. We're sorry we missed the mark, this is not our standard of service at all. We have a gift card for your next visit at the bar, just show us an ID that matches your open table reservation or payment to claim it. We appreciate your business and your feedback. Thanks for reaching out, we hope to see you soon.

reviews_data.review_text: Happened to be in the south end area on Jan 1 and was excited that folia was open on Wednesday unlike a lot of cute trendy places in Charlotte. I waited around at other south end classics like Vinyl, Stir, Charlotte bier garden etc. until 5ish so I could check out Folia. Unfortunately, when I showed up at 5ish, the door was closed. I waited around for ten minutes hoping they were just setting up in the back. No luck! As of 5:30 the doors are still closed! I’ve been waiting around at the Irish pub hoping the place would open, even checked their insta to see if I missed something. Super disappointed, I guess I’ll stick to the tried and true cocktail bars from now on.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Devon, we are so sorry about our miscommunication. We planned to be closed and the message wasn’t relayed properly. We hope you’ll consider trying us again. We will be open daily again beginning Thursday, Jan. 2nd.

reviews_data.review_text: If you are looking for a great cocktail and small plates Folia is a must. Amazing attention to detail. This place is run by some incredible people.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks so much for the glowing review! Hope to see you soon.

reviews_data.review_text:
Last night was my first time visiting Folia, and unfortunately, it didn’t leave a great impression. I had called ahead to make a reservation, but when we arrived, the hostess wasn’t particularly welcoming. When I inquired about the dress code, she simply said, "Don’t show up trashy."

The reservation was for two people, but when we arrived, we saw three friends waiting outside. I asked the hostess if they could join us, and after letting them in, I requested a larger table. The waitress, however, was very accommodating and moved us to a bigger, more private corner with two large couches and a swivel chair.

Later, my friend’s girlfriend arrived, bringing our group to six. Despite having ample space, the hostess rudely commented, “Oh, so now it’s six people?” The outdoor security staff also seemed to be getting an earful from her. We were just trying to have a relaxed evening with friends. When two people from our group left to go next door, we were down to four, but that didn’t stop the tension.

As we were finishing our last round of drinks, three more friends arrived and joined us at our table, as there was plenty of room. Suddenly, the indoor security guard approached, pointed at them, and told them they had to move to the bar—without any explanation or even asking me if it was okay for them to stay. There was no communication at all.

We decided to leave shortly after, feeling unwelcome due to the overly strict environment. I mentioned my frustration to our waitress, and she said she would get the manager, but no one came to address the issue.

Folia is a beautiful place with amazing drinks, but if you’re looking for a fun, social atmosphere, this is not the spot. We won’t be recommending it to anyone, and we definitely won’t be returning.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hello, thank you for taking the time leave the review. It looks like we missed the mark during your experience and we are very sorry for that. We aim for excellent experiences and we'd love an opportunity to make this right on your next visit. Please mention the name in this review in your next visit notes and we'll find a way to make this right for you. Cheers!

reviews_data.review_text: Been here several times, I bring a different friend each time so they can experience the WOW of walking through the hidden door for the first time. Always greeted very warmly. I love sitting near the water features, it feels like you're outside in nature. My three favorite drinks are the Pisco Sour, Mezcal Negroni and the Melon Smoke Show. They offer small bites. I love, love, love the octopus. I recommend coming with a small group or for a date.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks so much for the glowing review! We look forward to seeing you back soon.

reviews_data.review_text: came for a drink.. $17 for a sub par draft espresso martini😂🤡
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Riley, sorry we missed the mark for you. Thanks for the feedback, we are always open to growing and we value your input.

reviews_data.review_text: I had a great time at Folia last night. I had Folia & Flowers cocktail and it’s sooo good. I think it’s the best cocktail I’ve ever had in Charlotte. Absolutely delicious with rose water. Food menu is a little small but I hope they will add some more options soon. Interior is very stylish. Love it!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks so much Olya. We will keep your notes on the menu in mind as we grow. Hope to see you back soon!

reviews_data.review_text: We came here for an event so we didn't get any menu items. First off, when you walk in, it's like an adorable garden shed feel with a magical door leading into the main bar. The vibe is so relaxing and there are a variety of seating options from the bar to cozy little nooks. The cocktails are curated by one of Charlotte's best mixologists, Bob Peters. We got great service and would love to come back and try food and more cocktails.

reviews_data.review_text: Folia is so cutie! The service was great and the 2 cocktails I ordered were delicious. They have a really great mocktail menu as well- definitely will be back!

reviews_data.review_text: Went here for an event. Did not get food.  Got an old fashioned that was very good. Definitely want to visit when it’s not too busy.
The perfect spot to grab a crafted cocktail, glass of wine & small bites. My favorites were the octopus, ceviche w/ doritos (yes!), and mango sorbet. Great vibe, great team.
Been here twice and I love it. I love the zero proof menu. Such a vibe! 🥰
Great experience and belongs on the best 50 list! Make sure to ask for Sofia at the host stand for a good spot to seat, she’s the best.
Service was amazing, food was great, drinks were quality, and the atmosphere/ambience was amazing

I truly went here after driving by a few times to buy a plant so you can imagine my surprise when I found out it was a hidden cocktail bar. We went in anyway and had an absolutely lovely time - the zero-proof drinks were delicious and reasonably priced. I hope they can add some vegan food options so I can bring friends here for drinks and snacks!!
reviews_data.owner_answer: We're so glad you had a great visit! Thank you for your kind review!

reviews_data.review_text: My first experience at Folia was great. I loved how you can’t see the street because there are no windows—it made me feel exclusive, almost like a speakeasy. The bouncers also added to that exclusive vibe. The servers and staff were extremely friendly, and the ambiance was perfect, especially for a date night. The drinks were on par with a great Charlotte cocktail bar, and the food was even better. If you like unique small plates (try the octopus!), this place is for you.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you! We look forward to seeing you again soon

reviews_data.review_text:
This is one of the coolest speakeasies I've experienced. The entry way looks like a small plant shop and the wall opens up to reveal a really fun plant-themed bar.

They have fountains of water, comfortable seating, and pleasant ambient lighting which results in a great environment to enjoy a cocktail. You can choose from a wide array of unique cocktails which I think were very well executed!

They tend to be pretty busy later on Thurs / Fri / Sat nights, so you may want to make a reservation if you want a seat.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks, Jimmy!

reviews_data.review_text: A hidden gem you must attend. You won't be disappointed.

reviews_data.review_text: Great experience. Unique atmosphere like anything in Charlotte currently. Would also be a great spot for Private Events I imagine

reviews_data.review_text: Folia embodies the lively spirit of Miami with its vibrant decor and relaxed atmosphere. The drinks are outstanding, crafted with quality ingredients that truly impress. The friendly staff and upbeat music add to the overall experience, making it the perfect spot to unwind and enjoy the Charlotte nightlife. Highly recommend!
reviews_data.owner_answer: We’re grateful for your review and can’t wait to welcome you back soon!

reviews_data.review_text:
The Cocktail Bar is a vibrant addition to the downtown scene, perfectly situated for locals and visitors alike. The atmosphere strikes a balance between chic and cozy, with warm lighting and stylish decor that invites you to relax and enjoy.

The cocktail menu is a standout feature, offering a mix of classic favorites and inventive creations. Each drink is crafted with care, showcasing unique flavor combinations that elevate the experience. From refreshing spritzes to bold, complex mixes, there's something for everyone.

Overall, The Cocktail Bar is the perfect spot for a night out in the city, where great drinks and a welcoming vibe come together seamlessly.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Your support means the world to us, and we’re happy to hear you had such a great time!

reviews_data.review_text: Went the night after opening, fantastic service and atmosphere! Drinks were so creative and delicious. Highly recommended the ceviche and folia & flowers cocktail.
reviews_data.owner_answer: We truly appreciate your feedback and are so glad we could make your visit special!

reviews_data.review_text: One of the most beautiful cocktail bars I have ever been to. I got the Melon Smokeshow and it was absolutely perfect, smoky, and well balanced. I am definitely planning on making it one of my new regular spots!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much for your kind words! We're thrilled that you enjoyed your experience with us.

reviews_data.review_text: Folia is a gem! The atmosphere is stylish and cozy, the service is top-notch, and the cocktails are expertly crafted and delicious. If you’re after great drinks and a perfect vibe, Folia won’t disappoint!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for your wonderful review! We're so glad to hear that you enjoyed the atmosphere, service, and cocktails at Folia. It means a lot to us that you found everything to your liking, and we look forward to welcoming you back for more great drinks and good times!

raw_data.description:
Charlotte's most lush cocktail bar is now an ALL DAY cafe in the heart of South End. Start in the morning with coffee and espresso by local roaster Night Swim Coffee—plus flavored syrups and mushroom-based wellness shots—paired with savory and sweet breakfast bites by Built On Hospitality executive Chef Chris Coleman. The Noon & Night menu features bold, craveable flavors for lunch, dinner, and everything in between (and after).
Cocktail service begins at 10 a.m. on weekends and 2 p.m. on weekdays. Enjoy a Bob Peters creation with your brunch, afternoon calls, or when the workday is done. Reservations accepted and 21+ after 5pm, daily.

reviews_data.review_text: One star. Stopped by Folia on a Saturday night around 9pm after my phone died while waiting for an Uber. Security was fine, but the hostess staff was unhelpful and just got the manager, who immediately told me to leave instead of offering any assistance. I had cash in hand and just needed to charge my phone for a few minutes to get home safely. Really disappointed by how rude and dismissive the staff were—definitely not the hospitality I expected. Was looking forward to checking this place out eventually, but will not be returning.
Cocktail, foods, vibe, and service 10/10!!!!

review_questions.Noise level: Loud, but you can still talk

reviews_data.review_text: Too loud, slow and inconsiderate environment.

Cool concept, good service, pretty cocktails. Very aesthetic and so are the employees. I’d like to see a male bartender in tight shorts next time. Only con is that it’s difficult to have a conversation when it’s busy. It’s not a big place. You’re literally shoulder to shoulder at the bar. A bit uncomfortable for me and probably for the stranger next to me.

review_questions.Noise level: Loud, but you can still talk

reviews_data.review_text: This is a great place to stop in for a drink. The service I received from Kayleigh, Rylee, and Kaila was amazing and welcoming. 10/10 will be back.

Such an awesome experience! Highly recommend to anyone who wants amazing drinks, the prefect complement to flavorful, unique food, and a relaxed atmosphere. Think throwback without a smoky haze.
Kayleigh was very attentive and responded to our every request quickly, with a smile, and was so knowledgeable about the menu, beverage options, and even neighborhood stories!

Folia is a fabulous place to meet up with friends. Very interesting and upscale but warm and inviting. Food and drinks a top notch! And a special shout out for Kayleigh! She is the best and we always try to go when she is there! Makes the best drinks and is so gregarious, funny and always makes you feel like you belong there!!!
Really cute aesthetic. Best Paloma in Charlotte. Bartender Truly was super nice.
Neat place. Check it out!

review_questions.Seating type: Indoor dining area, Bar area, Booth seating, Counter seating

reviews_data.review_text: This was my first visit to this place, and our server, named“Truly,” was amazing! My girlfriend and I both ordered mocktails, and she created personalized drinks that perfectly matched our preferences. The ambiance, the service, everything was exceptional. I highly recommend this place and will definitely be returning.

I liked this place! Nice environment. We were seated quickly & ordered our drinks, however, our server didn’t come back to ask us if we wanted another even after our drinks were completely empty for quite some time. Drinks were super good!

Atmospherically, I’m sure Folia checks a lot of boxes for cocktail enthusiasts but for a small plate restaurant this is not it.
I made reservations for brunch for my sister’s birthday and when we arrived the greeting could not have been more lackluster. This place is not as advertised.

Brunch was uninspired, and the lack of atmosphere (at least on this Sunday)  made us feel like we weren’t even supposed there. They feature a small menu offering for brunch (which I’m sure might have been great had they not been out of half the menu items on a Sunday for brunch service especially when you open at 12pm)

Our server was very apologetic for the lackluster experience (we didn’t even bring it up) so we had a drink, got the one thing on the menu that was available, and went elsewhere. Save your time and your money.
Great time and intimate setting. Good vibes.
Service was fantastic. Drinks were great, even the mocktails.

The drinks, service and atmosphere are absolute perfection. The sitting areas are comfortable and clean and the noise and music were at a perfect conversational level.
It’s like sitting in the nicest cozy living room where a sweet friend brings you their signature cocktails durning a dinner party.
10 out of 10…BRILLIANT job, Folia! My new fav cocktail bar, hands down.
Like a gardening store speakeasy , very cute! The cocktails were amazing! I was shocked it wasn’t busy at all.
Marjorie was the best!
Mediocre. The atmosphere is ok, nothing special. Couldn’t even get a drink or food because the bartender refused to serve my group. So many better places in Charlotte!
Skip the food and just get coctails.

I understand that Folia is classified as a speakeasy due to its unique entryway—walking through a stylish plant shop before it opens up into the cocktail lounge definitely adds to the intrigue. However, the large glass window clearly showing the bar takes away from that hidden gem, secretive feel I typically associate with a true speakeasy.

The overall ambiance is calming, modern, and unique, making it a nice spot to relax. The cocktails were tasty, but nothing stood out beyond what I’ve had at other cocktail bars. One downside was the lack of a personalized experience—despite having a reservation, no one was at the front to greet us. After waiting nearly 10 minutes, we opened the door ourselves and were simply told to sit wherever we wanted, which diminished that tailored, exclusive touch.

While it’s a cute spot worth checking out, I wouldn’t classify it as a must-see compared to other options in the area.
Christina was so amazing! The drinks were so good and I loved the vibes.
Christina was an excellent server! She made our night ✨🤍 such a cozy vibe

Went for my husband birthday. The staff gave him a bday card and they all signed it. Super surprised by the gesture. The ace is awesome. Ask the bartender to make you an old fashion with elder flower, you wont be disappointed
Atmosphere and vibe was great.  Didn’t get any food just cocktails at the bar.  Drinks were weak and expensive and served by inexperienced bartender.  With tip, 4 drinks were $100.

A Miami oasis of good vibes, delicious small bites, and outstanding cocktails has found its way to SouthEnd and it’s going to be the place to be in Charlotte!

What you can enjoy: Food menu crafted by chef @tylerjordanlong and a cocktail menu crafted by @bobpeters.

MUST-order snack: Octopus — aji amarillo, espelette, and lime (Incredible!!!!)

From the bar, to the patio-like couch seating with water features, and the speakeasy-like lounge seating in the back of the bar, every nook and cranny was perfectly thought out. Come for the well crafted cocktail menu (with non alcoholic options) and stay for the small bites and great service. Pro tip: You can make reservations on Open Table.

I was so excited when I first walked into this lounge being it was my first time coming here. I was hoping to have a great experience since the ambiance and music seemed to be on point but I was rather disappointed from the moment I walked in. The customer service was awful and my friends were treated horribly by the bartender and even management. They had not ordered any drinks and the bartender refused to serve them and said they were intoxicated which wasn't the case at all. Even the security was super rude and made me feel uncomfortable. I had high hopes for this establishment but due to my experience I will not be back.
Very rude staff. Really ruined my experience there
Amazing vibes and unique cocktails. I can't get over how much this place makes me feel like I'm in Blanche Devereaux's floral bedroom...in the absolute best way!
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Amy, all we have to say is: "Thank you for being a friend."
:) 

See you soon!

reviews_data.review_text: A green and floral paradise, with beautiful tropical, bohemian touches throughout the space with amazing service, music, vibes and cocktails! Great spot for date day or date night or to meet up with friends for a little social happy hour! My husband and I went here for our day date and enjoyed some "annuals"- Folia's cocktails that are here for the season. We were thoroughly impressed by the service, the friendliness of the staff and the cocktails themselves! There is an art to making a great cocktail and Folia has done it well! We tried the Honey Franciulli; Drink Ses-a-me, Morning Bourbon! and Banana Nut Bread. All had amazing flavor profiles! Definitely a must try for anyone looking for chill/lounge vibes, some fresh cocktails and plants all-around! *They also have small bites/small plates as well, including a brunch menu served till 3pm on weekends. We tried the Cucumber Avocado Toast (from their brunch menu) and the Octopus (from their regular menu)- both very delish! Thank you for making our day date so much fun! Can't wait to go back!

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Octopus, Banana Nut Bread, Honey Franciulli

reviews_data.review_text: When my boyfriend and I walked into the door the older lady at the hostess stand was very rude. When we entered the door we were not greeted, but instead just stared at until I said hello. Keep in mind it was only my boyfriend and I and the hostess standing there. I don’t know what her issue was, but it was like she looked at us like we did not belong there. When we got seated, I will say our bartender Eric saved the day! Eric was great, engaging, and make wonderful cocktails. The hostess lady really put a bad taste in our mouth….

Please know that we take your feedback very seriously and will address this matter with our team to ensure that all our guests receive the friendly and courteous service they deserve from the moment they walk through our doors.

We are thrilled to hear that Eric was able to turn your experience around with his exceptional service and fantastic cocktails. We'll be sure to pass along your kind words to him—it's always wonderful to know when our team members make a positive impact.

We hope you’ll give us another opportunity to serve you in the future and provide the five-star experience we aim for with every visit.

Cheers, 
Team Folia

We do typically work off of reservations so sometimes it does take us a minute to sort through our systems and make sure we are honoring the space we have already promised to guests. I know it appears like we are just pouring drinks on tap, but those are batched cocktails made with house squeezed juices and freshly made syrups. While they do save us time in service, we still put a lot of love into those and use only top quality ingredients. We do appreciate your input and we will try to find ways to add value and make excellent experiences happen for you in the future. Please get in touch any time to book your next reservation or special event!

reviews_data.review_text: Beautiful cocktail bar, a great staff & amazing drinks! Perfect place for a girls night out or a date night. Always enjoy my time here.

reviews_data.review_text: I love this place. The vibe walking in is always so welcoming. The staff is amazing, ready and willing to ensure you are happy and feel safe in their environment. Can't wait to go again. Of course plants are just amazing.
Amazing atmosphere and super friendly staff!

I liked the bar esthetic but security is overly aggressive. Also, very slow service.

they didn’t let us in and none of us were intoxicated whatsoever (I promise we had 3 people not drinking at all). They thought they were better than every other bar. I would not go to this bar unless you’re looking to be turned away. Too “prestigious” for my taste. There’s so many better places to go in Charlotte. I will never go back.

The atmosphere here is amazing! The cocktails tasted great, however, at this price point I aimed for a more elevated presentation. We only tried their brunch menu--egg Salad was fantastic and the flatbread was pretty good too.

I recently celebrated my birthday at Folia, and while the entire experience was fantastic, the highlight of our visit was definitely Bria! reviews_data.review_text:
Beautiful place. Peaceful atmosphere. Great friendly bartender Erik made us feel welcomed on our our first visit and made great drinks
Will definitely return 👍👍

Loved this place!!!! The host shout out to her she was amazing!!!!!!! BUT FYI the server did not want to mention the 50 dollar truffle when I went to order the baguette. She never mentioned it was a "special" she just asked if I wanted "caviar or truffle". When I get my bill and see for our server to not mention the truffle being an EXTRA $50 for a $9 baguette was messed up. But overall loved the place will be back and not ordered the truffle 🙌🏽

We went as a group of friends to celebrate my birthday and unfortunately it was overall a rough experience. Although the cocktails and the ambiance/design were very nice the operations and service was VERY poor. Where we had made our reservation for (the green room) which open table specifically had you pick when you make a reservation, we were not sat there. When inquiring about our seating the manager said you cannot request places to sit…so this was just untrue which felt quite sketchy. They gave us a champagne toast to compensate which was nice however. After that the drinks were great but with a party of 4 they came up to our table and told us we had to leave that the next party was there and waiting in the lobby. We hadn’t even been seated for an hour and a half yet. The manager then came up again after we said we needed to then cancel our drink order if we were being kicked out. She apologized and said we could stay and gave us some drinks but just sent us 2 drinks for a party of 4. It was all very uncomfortable and we felt like we were on a time although it doesn’t say a time limit or anything on the reservations. They didn’t have the proper ingredients on a busy Saturday night to make an espresso martini (arguably one of the most popular cocktails right now) and it was quite bad. The manager did try to apologize and check on us but at that point it was just uncomfortable and we were ready to go anyways. I would like to go again when they become better with service and operations and give more specific instructions on what their reservations look like as the ambiance and cocktails were good but this specific experience was poor.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hello, Thanks for taking the time to share your feedback. We're sorry we missed the mark, this is not our standard of service at all. We have a gift card for your next visit at the bar, just show us an ID that matches your open table reservation or payment to claim it. We appreciate your business and your feedback. Thanks for reaching out, we hope to see you soon.

reviews_data.review_text: Happened to be in the south end area on Jan 1 and was excited that folia was open on Wednesday unlike a lot of cute trendy places in Charlotte. I waited around at other south end classics like Vinyl, Stir, Charlotte bier garden etc. until 5ish so I could check out Folia. Unfortunately, when I showed up at 5ish, the door was closed. I waited around for ten minutes hoping they were just setting up in the back. No luck! As of 5:30 the doors are still closed! I’ve been waiting around at the Irish pub hoping the place would open, even checked their insta to see if I missed something. Super disappointed, I guess I’ll stick to the tried and true cocktail bars from now on.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Devon, we are so sorry about our miscommunication. We planned to be closed and the message wasn’t relayed properly. We hope you’ll consider trying us again. We will be open daily again beginning Thursday, Jan. 2nd.

reviews_data.review_text: If you are looking for a great cocktail and small plates Folia is a must. Amazing attention to detail. This place is run by some incredible people.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks so much for the glowing review! Hope to see you soon.

reviews_data.review_text:
Last night was my first time visiting Folia, and unfortunately, it didn’t leave a great impression. I had called ahead to make a reservation, but when we arrived, the hostess wasn’t particularly welcoming. When I inquired about the dress code, she simply said, "Don’t show up trashy."

The reservation was for two people, but when we arrived, we saw three friends waiting outside. I asked the hostess if they could join us, and after letting them in, I requested a larger table. The waitress, however, was very accommodating and moved us to a bigger, more private corner with two large couches and a swivel chair.

Later, my friend’s girlfriend arrived, bringing our group to six. Despite having ample space, the hostess rudely commented, “Oh, so now it’s six people?” The outdoor security staff also seemed to be getting an earful from her. We were just trying to have a relaxed evening with friends. When two people from our group left to go next door, we were down to four, but that didn’t stop the tension.

As we were finishing our last round of drinks, three more friends arrived and joined us at our table, as there was plenty of room. Suddenly, the indoor security guard approached, pointed at them, and told them they had to move to the bar—without any explanation or even asking me if it was okay for them to stay. There was no communication at all.

We decided to leave shortly after, feeling unwelcome due to the overly strict environment. I mentioned my frustration to our waitress, and she said she would get the manager, but no one came to address the issue.

Folia is a beautiful place with amazing drinks, but if you’re looking for a fun, social atmosphere, this is not the spot. We won’t be recommending it to anyone, and we definitely won’t be returning.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hello, thank you for taking the time leave the review. It looks like we missed the mark during your experience and we are very sorry for that. We aim for excellent experiences and we'd love an opportunity to make this right on your next visit. Please mention the name in this review in your next visit notes and we'll find a way to make this right for you. Cheers!

reviews_data.review_text: Been here several times, I bring a different friend each time so they can experience the WOW of walking through the hidden door for the first time. Always greeted very warmly. I love sitting near the water features, it feels like you're outside in nature. My three favorite drinks are the Pisco Sour, Mezcal Negroni and the Melon Smoke Show. They offer small bites. I love, love, love the octopus. I recommend coming with a small group or for a date.

Absolutely delicious with rose water. Food menu is a little small but I hope they will add some more options soon. Interior is very stylish. Love it!

reviews_data.review_text: We came here for an event so we didn't get any menu items. First off, when you walk in, it's like an adorable garden shed feel with a magical door leading into the main bar. The vibe is so relaxing and there are a variety of seating options from the bar to cozy little nooks. The cocktails are curated by one of Charlotte's best mixologists, Bob Peters. We got great service and would love to come back and try food and more cocktails.

reviews_data.review_text: My first experience at Folia was great. I loved how you can’t see the street because there are no windows—it made me feel exclusive, almost like a speakeasy. reviews_data.review_text:
The Cocktail Bar is a vibrant addition to the downtown scene, perfectly situated for locals and visitors alike. The atmosphere strikes a balance between chic and cozy, with warm lighting and stylish decor that invites you to relax and enjoy.

The cocktail menu is a standout feature, offering a mix of classic favorites and inventive creations. Each drink is crafted with care, showcasing unique flavor combinations that elevate the experience. From refreshing spritzes to bold, complex mixes, there's something for everyone.

Overall, The Cocktail Bar is the perfect spot for a night out in the city, where great drinks and a welcoming vibe come together seamlessly.

raw_data.description:
Charlotte's most lush cocktail bar is now an ALL DAY cafe in the heart of South End. Start in the morning with coffee and espresso by local roaster Night Swim Coffee—plus flavored syrups and mushroom-based wellness shots—paired with savory and sweet breakfast bites by Built On Hospitality executive Chef Chris Coleman. The Noon & Night menu features bold, craveable flavors for lunch, dinner, and everything in between (and after).
Cocktail service begins at 10 a.m. on weekends and 2 p.m. on weekdays. Enjoy a Bob Peters creation with your brunch, afternoon calls, or when the workday is done. Reservations accepted and 21+ after 5pm, daily.
